# Vue SFC Rules

## Structure

- Add a name in a `<script lang="ts">` block at the top of the file.
- Use `<script lang="ts" setup>` for all logic (note: `lang` before `setup`).
- Use `<template>` for markup, keep it concise and readable.
- Place styles in `<style lang="scss" scoped>` unless global.

## Best Practices

- Use PascalCase for component file names and names.
- Export only one component per file.
- Use props and emits with full TypeScript typing.
- Use composables for reusable logic.
- Keep components focused and small; split large components.

## Example

```vue
<script lang="ts">
export default {
  name: "MyComponent",
};
</script>

<script lang="ts" setup>
interface Props {
  onClick: () => void;
}

const props = defineProps<Props>();
</script>

<template>
  <button @click="props.onClick">Click me</button>
</template>

<style lang="scss" scoped>
button {
  color: $primary;
}
</style>
```
